recordings.loc: Cusick Creek Drainage, Bannock County, Idaho
recordings.rmk:
This recording is not modified. Two adult Red-breasted Nuthatches were foraging within the range of 5-30 feet away in Douglas fir habitat bordered by open sagebrush slopes. The birds were calling quietly, a small repertoire of chip and twiddle call notes. They foraged along the trunk and branches of the Douglas firs during the recording. The associated with each other, following each other from tree to tree and sometimes from branch to branch. Often, however, they foraged independently.
In the recording, the city of Pocatello can be heard miles below and the birds' feet and bills can be heard moving against the bark.
